Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of
@salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Thinly slice @chives{a few}. Pick @parsley{some} leaves
from stems; finely chop leaves. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with 1 tsp @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp}
(2 tsp for 4 servings), @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> You'll use the remaining Italian Seasoning later.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Transfer chicken to a #baking sheet{}. Top with half the @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2}(sliced)
(save the rest for serving).

Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through and cheese melts, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @Spaghetti{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Keep empty pot handy for step 5.

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat.
Add tomato and remaining @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until slightly
softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Balsamic Vinegar{5%tbsp} and @Sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings). Simmer
until mixture is slightly thickened, ~{1%minute}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Stir in chives and
chopped parsley; season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Melt @Butter{2%tbsp} in pot used for pasta over low heat. Stir in garlic; cook until
fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add drained spaghetti, 2 TBSP reserved pasta cooking water, and @Butter{1%tbsp}. Toss
to thoroughly combine. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise if desired.

Divide spaghetti between #bowls{} and top with chicken. Spoon balsamic tomato over
chicken. Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella and serve.